<title>USA: Pratt &amp; Whitney said will buy Howmet plants.</title>
<headline>Pratt &amp; Whitney said will buy Howmet plants.</headline>
<dateline>EAST HARTFORD, Conn. 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>United Technologies Corp's Pratt &amp; Whitney said Wednesday it agreed to buy Howmet Corp's airfoil refurbishment plants in Wichita Falls, Texas, Claremore, Oklahoma and North Haven, Connecticut.</p>
<p>Terms of the deal were not disclosed.</p>
<p>Howmet said its refurbishment operation, which repairs engine-run turbine components, accounts for about six percent of its annual sales.</p>
<p>Howmet is owned by a joint venture of Carlyle Group and Thiokol Corp.</p>
